<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="420">Abos, Girolamo (baptismal name Geronimo), Maltese composer; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="418" RE="Nov. 16, 1715" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="414" predict="birth">b.</Birth> Valetta, <Date gate:gateId="331" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">Nov. 16, 1715</Date></Event_Birth>; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="419" RE="May, 1760" Pred="death" Pred-tyoe="time"><Death gate:gateId="415" predict="death">d.</Death> <Location gate:gateId="332" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="332;336;339;341;345" rule2="LocFinal">Naples</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="333" rule1="DateName" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">May, 1760</Date></Event_Birth>. He studied with Leonardo Leo and Francesco Durante in <Location gate:gateId="336" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="332;336;339;341;345" rule2="LocFinal">Naples</Location>. In <Date gate:gateId="337" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1756</Date> he went to <Location gate:gateId="338" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="338;343" rule2="LocFinal">London</Location> as &apos;maestro al cembalo&apos; at the Italian Theater. Returning to <Location gate:gateId="339" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="332;336;339;341;345" rule2="LocFinal">Naples</Location> in <Date gate:gateId="340" rule1="YearContext1" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">1758</Date> he taught at the Cons, della Pieta de&apos; Turchini. Among his pupils was Paisiello. Abos _ wrote 14 operas which were produced in <Location gate:gateId="341" locType="city" rule1="InLoc1" gate:matches="332;336;339;341;345" rule2="LocFinal">Naples</Location>, <Location gate:gateId="342" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Rome</Location> and <Location gate:gateId="343" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="338;343" rule2="LocFinal">London</Location>; of these, Tito Manlio (<Location gate:gateId="345" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="332;336;339;341;345" rule2="LocFinal">Naples</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="346" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">May 30, 1751</Date>) was successful; also composed 7 masses and other church music. He is often confused with his contemporary, the Neapolitan opera composer, Giuseppe Avossa (<Date gate:gateId="348" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1716</Date></paragraph>